              </svg>
              View on GitHub
          </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Project 5 -->
      <div class="project-item" data-project="5">
        <div class="project-number">05</div>
        <div class="project-content">
          <div class="project-header">
          <h2 class="sigmar-ff project-title">SNAKES HASH IDENTIFIER</h2>
            <span class="project-category">Security • Cryptography</span>
          </div>
          
          <p class="comfortaa-regular project-description">
            A Python-based tool that detects and classifies different cryptographic hash values. This utility 
            supports identifying various hashing algorithms like MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, and more using pattern 
            matching and hash length analysis. Essential for security researchers, ethical hackers, and 
            developers working with cryptographic systems.
          </p>

          <div class="project-details">
            <div class="project-tech-stack">
              <span class="tech-label">Tech Stack:</span>
              <div class="tech-tags">
                <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
                <span class="tech-tag">Cryptography</span>
                <span class="tech-tag">Security</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="project-features-section">
              <h3 class="features-title">Key Features</h3>
          <ul class="project-features">
                <li>Pattern matching for accurate hash identification</li>
                <li>Supports multiple hash algorithms (MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, etc.)</li>
            <li>Designed for security researchers and ethical hackers</li>
                <li>Fast and efficient hash analysis</li>
          </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="project-links">
